<h2 id="org3c9cc03">Evil Mode</h2>
<div class="outline-text-2" id="text-org3c9cc03">
<p>
Emacs evil mode is a package for vimmers who see the power of emacs.
</p>
</div>


<div id="outline-container-orgb5909a8" class="outline-3">
<h3 id="orgb5909a8">Disable evil mode for certain modes</h3>
<div class="outline-text-3" id="text-orgb5909a8">
<p>
Some modes do not require the use of evil-mode and infact are just single key commands.
</p>

<p>
<a href="20230515224412-elfeed.html#ID-1561f948-9a4d-4936-a58f-90a6b87ddb06">Elfeed</a> is such a package that doesnt mesh with evil.
</p>

<p>
Use the <code>evil-set-inital-state</code> function to set a state or use <code>turn-off-evil-mode</code>
</p>

<p>
Disable evil for elfeed.
</p>
<div class="org-src-container">
<pre class="src src-emacs-lisp">(add-hook 'elfeed-search-mode-hook 'turn-off-evil-mode)
(add-hook 'elfeed-show-mode-hook 'turn-off-evil-mode)
</pre>
</div>
